<paragraph blockId="15.[113,764,919,1007]" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis box="[151,257,919,943]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Etymology</emphasis>
. – The adjectival epithet 
<taxonomicName box="[515,670,919,943]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[515,670,919,943]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in reference to the earlier confusion of this species with the closely related 
<taxonomicName box="[192,321,983,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[192,321,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Notes).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[113,764,1047,1199]" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis box="[151,405,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. – Known only from near Amporoforo, c. 
<quantity box="[225,291,1079,1103]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
inland from Madagascar’s southeastern coast between the towns of Vohipeno and Farafangana (
<figureCitation box="[682,751,1111,1135]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[136,167,1313,1332]" captionTargetBox="[136,786,276,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-581@4.[136,786,276,1292]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. – Geographic distribution of Memecylon complanatum R.D. Stone (closed circle), M. convergens R.D. Stone (closed diamonds), M. fofifa R.D. Stone (open circles), M. longipetiolatum R.D. Stone (open square), M. paraxenum R.D. Stone (closed star), M. potamicum R.D. Stone (closed triangle), M. pseudogaleatum R.D. Stone (closed cross), M. subchartaceum R.D. Stone (open stars), and M. unguiculare R.D. Stone (closed square), mapped on the bioclimatic zones of Madagascar (after CORNET, 1974; see SCHATZ, 2000)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683763" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683763/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Habitat in remnants of humid forest on laterite, elevation c. 
<specimenCount box="[138,197,1175,1199]" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" type="generic">
<quantity box="[138,194,1175,1199]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" unit="m" value="25.0">25 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[113,764,1239,1551]" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis box="[151,351,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Conservation status</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[383,660,1239,1263]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[383,660,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Memecylon pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from a single location with an AOO of 
<quantity box="[562,619,1271,1295]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" unit="km" value="4.0">4 km</quantity>
². Given that the forests of the coastal region around Farafangana have been largely destroyed or reduced to small remnants, and that 
<taxonomicName box="[170,381,1367,1391]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[170,381,1367,1391]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been seen in more than 60 years, it is quite possible that the species is already extinct, although additional field-work would be needed to verify this. 
<taxonomicName box="[166,447,1463,1487]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[166,447,1463,1487]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Memecylon pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thus provisionally assessed as “Critically Endangered” [CR B2ab(iii)] in accordance with the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[599,738,1527,1551]" firstAuthor="IUCN" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" refId="ref12323" refString="IUCN (2012). IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 3.1. Ed. 2. IUCN Species Survival Commission, IUCN, Gland &amp; Cambridge." type="book" year="2012">IUCN, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[113,766,1591,1935]" lastBlockId="15.[801,1454,279,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis box="[151,208,1592,1615]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[244,531,1591,1615]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[244,531,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Memecylon pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[588,722,1591,1615]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[588,722,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are clearly very close, as evidenced by the fact that the flowering specimen 
<emphasis box="[224,469,1655,1679]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Service Forestier 15244</emphasis>
(TEF), designated here as the 
<typeStatus box="[155,249,1687,1711]" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">holotype</typeStatus>
of the new species, was previously annotated by R. Capuron as an unnamed variety of the latter. Compared with typical 
<taxonomicName box="[250,383,1751,1775]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[250,383,1751,1775]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the material of 
<taxonomicName box="[564,763,1751,1775]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[564,763,1751,1775]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having young branchlets subquadrangular to terete (not compressed and laterally grooved on the two faces), smaller flowers with petals obcordate (vs. broadly ovate), and fruits bilaterally asymmetrical (in this respect more similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[145,314,1911,1935]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bezavonense">
<emphasis box="[145,314,1911,1935]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. bezavonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the newly described 
<taxonomicName box="[606,758,1912,1935]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="convergens">
<emphasis box="[606,758,1912,1935]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. convergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, q.v.). The type locality of 
<taxonomicName box="[1079,1279,279,303]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[1079,1279,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Amporoforo is also disjunct by 
<quantity box="[1008,1086,311,335]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" unit="km" value="375.0">375 km</quantity>
from the nearest known locality of 
<taxonomicName box="[833,970,343,367]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[833,970,343,367]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the Vatomandry district of 
<collectingRegion country="Madagascar" name="Toamasina" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Toamasina province</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[801,1454,279,1327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">
It should be further noted that the P sheet of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Service Forestier 13908</emphasis>
, cited here as a 
<typeStatus box="[1125,1217,439,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1252,1447,439,463]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[1252,1447,439,463]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was previously determined by M. Jacques-Félix as 
<taxonomicName box="[1323,1446,471,495]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pileatum">
<emphasis box="[1323,1446,471,495]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pileatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This material would also key to 
<taxonomicName box="[1132,1256,503,527]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pileatum">
<emphasis box="[1132,1256,503,527]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pileatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="JACQUES-FELIX" firstAuthor="JACQUES-FELIX" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" pagination="383 - 451" refId="ref12450" refString="JACQUES-FELIX, H. (1985 a). Les Memecyleae (Melastomataceae) de Madagascar (1 re partie). Bull. Mus. Natl. Hist. Nat., B, Adansonia 6: 383 - 451." type="journal article" year="1985" yearSuffix="a">JACQUES-FÉLIX (1985a)</bibRefCitation>
on account of having young branchlets terete (not compressed) and fruits 17–18 × 
<quantity box="[1149,1265,566,591]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="21.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="21.0">21–22 mm</quantity>
(not 14 × 
<quantity box="[1379,1451,567,591]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
as cited by him for 
<taxonomicName box="[1021,1156,599,623]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[1021,1156,599,623]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, terete branchlets can no longer be used as a diagnostic character for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pileatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pileatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
since this feature is shared with 
<taxonomicName box="[1248,1446,663,687]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[1248,1446,663,687]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, the dimensions of the fruit are not a good character to distinguish between 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1258,727,751]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[1124,1258,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1272,1403,727,751]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pileatum">
<emphasis box="[1272,1403,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pileatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[801,992,759,783]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[801,992,759,783]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For example, the collection 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Service Forestier 28157</emphasis>
(K, MO, P, TEF), which was cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="JACQUES-FELIX" firstAuthor="JACQUES-FELIX" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" pagination="383 - 451" refId="ref12450" refString="JACQUES-FELIX, H. (1985 a). Les Memecyleae (Melastomataceae) de Madagascar (1 re partie). Bull. Mus. Natl. Hist. Nat., B, Adansonia 6: 383 - 451." type="journal article" year="1985" yearSuffix="a">JACQUES-FÉLIX (1985a)</bibRefCitation>
under 
<taxonomicName box="[952,1081,823,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[952,1081,823,847]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has fruits of c. 23 × 
<quantity box="[1301,1377,823,847]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
. Additional confirmation that the mature fruits of 
<taxonomicName box="[1283,1413,855,879]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[1283,1413,855,879]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are indeed much larger than was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="JACQUES-FELIX" firstAuthor="JACQUES-FELIX" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" pagination="383 - 451" refId="ref12450" refString="JACQUES-FELIX, H. (1985 a). Les Memecyleae (Melastomataceae) de Madagascar (1 re partie). Bull. Mus. Natl. Hist. Nat., B, Adansonia 6: 383 - 451." type="journal article" year="1985" yearSuffix="a">JACQUES-FÉLIX (1985a)</bibRefCitation>
is provided by several recent collections determined by me as belonging to this species (viz. 
<emphasis box="[1232,1414,951,975]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Razanatsima 170</emphasis>
, K, MO; 
<emphasis box="[860,1092,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Rakotoarivelo et al. 574</emphasis>
, MO, NU; and 
<emphasis box="[1257,1447,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">Antilahimena 8125</emphasis>
, MO). Even the character of the anther connectives, said by 
<bibRefCitation author="JACQUES-FELIX" box="[801,1043,1042,1071]" firstAuthor="JACQUES-FELIX" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" pagination="383 - 451" refId="ref12450" refString="JACQUES-FELIX, H. (1985 a). Les Memecyleae (Melastomataceae) de Madagascar (1 re partie). Bull. Mus. Natl. Hist. Nat., B, Adansonia 6: 383 - 451." type="journal article" year="1985" yearSuffix="a">JACQUES-FÉLIX (1985a)</bibRefCitation>
to be conical in 
<taxonomicName box="[1214,1341,1047,1071]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[1214,1341,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and subulate in 
<taxonomicName box="[878,1007,1079,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pileatum">
<emphasis box="[878,1007,1079,1103]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pileatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, does not hold up to added scrutiny. On the other hand, the differing leaf dimensions of 
<taxonomicName box="[1321,1452,1111,1135]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[1321,1452,1111,1135]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[849,978,1143,1167]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pileatum">
<emphasis box="[849,978,1143,1167]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pileatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are a seemingly useful character, i.e., leaves smaller 6–9(–12.5) × 3–4.5(–7.5) cm in the former vs. larger 12.5 –15.5 × 
<quantity box="[931,1051,1206,1231]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" unit="cm" value="7.0" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="6.5">6.5–7.5 cm</quantity>
in the latter. The leaf dimensions of 
<taxonomicName box="[801,992,1239,1263]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogaleatum">
<emphasis box="[801,992,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pseudogaleatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as per the above description) fit well within the specified range of 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1177,1271,1295]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galeatum">
<emphasis box="[1044,1177,1271,1295]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. galeatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but are too small to be a good match for 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1099,1303,1327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pileatum">
<emphasis box="[973,1099,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="234">M. pileatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
